          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "1-mm-thick solid hydrogen target"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The energies and angles of the",
                "recoiling tritons were measured by an array of four",
                "MUST2 telescopes located 30 cm downstream of the",
                "target. Each telescope, with an active area of 10x10",
                "cm2, consisted of a 0.3 mm thick double-sided Si",
                "strip detector and a 4 cm thick 16-fold CsI calorimeter",
                "The dE detector was divided into 256 strips in both",
                "the x and y directions, providing position information."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The reaction products emitted at small angles",
                "were detected with a SPEG spectrometer"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Particle identification of light particles was",
                "made by the dE-E method. The total kinetic energy",
                "was obtained as a sum of the energy information (E+dE)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A triple coincidence with the 16O beam, the",
                "recoiling tritons, and the beamlike ejectiles of either",
                "14-O (for the bound states of 14-O) or 13N (for the",
                "unbound states of 14O above the proton separation",
                "energy. The ejectiles were detected by SPEG or a",
                "Si dE-E telescope."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Correction for energy loss in the target was made in",
                "determination of total kinetic energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The secondary 14-O beam at 51 AMeV was",
                "produced by fragmentation of 16-O at 90 AMeV on a",
                "920 mg/cm2 thick C target located in the SISSI",
                "device.The Alpha fragment separator, equipped with a",
                "135 mg/cm2 thick Al degrader, was used to purify the",
                "fragments.The purity (intensity) of the O-14 beam",
                "was around 40% (6.0E+4 pps)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Missing mass method was used to study the structure",
                "of 12-O."
              ]
            }
          ],
